Show HN: IP Guide – info on IP addresses, Networks, and ASNs
description:
Hey all, wanted to share my recent weekend hack project. I wanted to improve upon the existing space for looking up information about IP addresses and ASNs.

The backend is written in Rust and pulls BGP data every 8 hours from the RIPE RIS project to build up a routing table and also adds geolocation information. The frontend is using React and Tailscale.

Would love any feedback or suggestions on what to improve.

Ask HN: How should I setup a phone for a newly blind relative?
description:
I am home for the holidays and my grandfather is newly blind. He's never learned braille or anything else and I believe it can be a relatively isolating experience. While I'm in town for the holidays, I would love to help him get back into things like podcasts, audio books and WhatsApp. Does anyone have recommendations for how to help set this up?

He currently has an iPhone but if android phones are superior for blind users, I would happily help him switch.

Stripe Threatening to Disrupt Our Business
description:
We are a motorcycle track day event organizer company - Precision Track Day (https://precisiontrackday.org/) and currently use stripe to process payments

All what we do is rent tracks, and then sell tickets to these tracks so people can come have a great time riding their motorcycles on how its meant to be ridden

However,recently stripe told us in extrememly vague terms that we are doing something that we should not be doing and we are a restricted business.

Their specific words were "pecifically, we are unable to accept payments for stored value or credits maintained, accepted, and issued by anyone other than the seller, as mentioned on our Restricted Businesses list."

This is after explaining to them that there are no other sellers except us - our customers (riders) they only deal with us and not anyone else
